# Cursor Rules — Stock Management App

This repository is a standards-driven engineering system. Follow every rule below strictly.

## Project Identity

- **Stack**: Next.js 16 (App Router, static export) · Mantine 9 · Dexie.js (IndexedDB) · Zustand · TypeScript
- **Architecture**: Offline-first, local-first. No backend. All data persists in IndexedDB via Dexie.js.
- **Target**: Mobile-first, touch-optimized, premium native-like UX.
- **CRITICAL**: Do NOT add `fetch` calls to a non-existent API. Use domain service files under `src/features/<domain>/services/`.

## Next.js Rules

- This is NOT the Next.js you know. Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing code.
- Static export only (`output: 'export'`). No API routes. No server-side features.
- Set `'use client'` at the highest page/layout node, not per-file.

## Architecture (Feature-Sliced Design)

```
src/
├── app/          # App Router pages, global providers
├── features/     # Domain modules (inventory, invoices)
│   └── <domain>/
│       ├── components/
│       ├── hooks/
│       └── services/
├── shared/       # Truly global primitives only
└── types/        # Global TypeScript definitions
```

- Features must NEVER import internal components/hooks from other features.
- Only multi-domain primitives belong in `src/shared/`.

## React Engineering Standards

- Pure components where possible. Avoid unnecessary rerenders.
- NEVER use `useEffect` for derived calculations. Compute directly during render.
- NEVER duplicate state. Derive values from existing state/props.
- Use `useMemo`/`useCallback` only for measurable performance gains.
- Prefer composition (children, render props) over monolithic components.
- Zustand: Never consume the entire store. Export atomic selector hooks.
- Decouple search keystrokes from DB queries using deferred value hooks.

## Mantine Standards (UI Operating System)

- Mantine is the ONLY UI system. Use it exhaustively before creating anything custom.
- ALL spacing, colors, typography, radii, shadows MUST come from Mantine theme tokens.
- ZERO inline styles for static styling. Only dynamic calculations (virtualization offsets) excepted.
- Use Mantine primitives: `<Box>`, `<Stack>`, `<Group>`, `<Text>`, `<Title>`, `<Paper>`, `<Button>`.
- Layout via `gap` props, not margin hacks.
- Dark-mode ready: `var(--mantine-color-body)`, `var(--mantine-color-text)` — never hardcoded hex.
- Mobile-first: Safe area insets on fixed footers. 44px minimum touch targets.
- Do NOT create custom spacing systems, typography systems, or button systems.

## TypeScript Standards

- `any` is forbidden. ESLint enforces `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any`.
- Type-safe props. Extend Mantine's `BoxProps` or equivalent.
- No `as any`, no `as unknown as T` without documented justification.

## Performance Standards

- Virtualization mandatory for lists > 50 items (`@tanstack/react-virtual`).
- NEVER use `.toArray()` on full database tables. Use B-Tree indexes, `.limit()`.
- Lazy-load heavy deps (PDF generators, exporters) via dynamic `import()`.
- Always revoke Blob Object URLs on unmount or replacement.

## Forbidden Anti-Patterns

1. `onMouseEnter`/`onMouseLeave` for style changes → Use CSS hover states
2. `.toArray()` on full DB tables → Use indexed queries with `.limit()`
3. Business logic in DB hooks → Use explicit service layer with transactions
4. Inline `style={{ }}` for static values → Use Mantine theme props
5. `useEffect` for derived state → Compute during render
6. Whole Zustand store consumption → Use atomic selectors
7. `onClick` on `<div>` without semantics → Use `component="button"` polymorphism

## Quality Gates (ALL must pass)

```bash
npm run format      # Prettier
npm run lint        # ESLint
npm run type-check  # TypeScript compiler
npm run build       # Next.js production build
```

